[2024-11-15T09:30:00Z] Sarah: "Anyone knows why my Redis cache invalidation isn't working with Spring Boot? I'm using @CacheEvict but entries stay in cache"
[2024-11-15T09:35:00Z] Mike: "Check if you have @EnableCaching on your main class. Also:
@CacheEvict(value = 'users', key = '#user.id')
public void updateUser(User user) { ... }
Make sure the key matches what you used in @Cacheable"

